President Obama has announced the launch of competitions for new manufacturing innovation hubs and American apprenticeship grants. The goal is to improve the competitiveness of American businesses and workers by fostering new manufacturing innovations and providing workers with opportunities to expand their skill sets. The president will allocate nearly $400 million for these initiatives. The manufacturing innovation hubs will receive more than $290 million in public-private investment, while $100 million will be used to expand apprenticeships for American workers. The aim is to create new job opportunities and strengthen the middle class. The president also emphasized the need to reform the tax code and open up new markets abroad for American-made goods through fair trade agreements.